trend_summary: Built-up cover expands steadily, with new subdivisions and an enlarged southwest industrial zone, while cropland declines and pockets of forest regrow. A new reservoir and upgraded arterial roads reshape the southeast–west corridor. Despite growth, green space remains dominant, yielding an overall medium-density suburban landscape.
notable_changes: Industrial/commercial estate southwest of the highway interchange grows markedly, adding large white-roofed buildings.
Multiple curvilinear housing subdivisions spread north-central, filling former woodland gaps.
A brownish reservoir or quarry lake appears southeast of the center, replacing forest cover.
East–west connector road is widened and linked to a new interchange, improving network hierarchy.
Eastern cropland patches shrink, transitioning to mixed tree cover and low-density estates.
